50|$|One {{of the key}} {{features}} of <b>BCH</b> <b>codes</b> is that during code design, there is a precise control over the number of symbol errors correctable by the code. In particular, {{it is possible to}} design binary <b>BCH</b> <b>codes</b> that can correct multiple bit errors. Another advantage of <b>BCH</b> <b>codes</b> is the ease with which they can be decoded, namely, via an algebraic method known as syndrome decoding. This simplifies the design of the decoder for these codes, using small low-power electronic hardware.|$|R
